
/*
 * 1. The [get-value] slot retrieves the value of the node referenced by its expression argument.
 * 2. The expression `:x:@.fields` points to the first node named [.fields] relative to the current context.
 * 3. The result of [get-value] will be the value stored in the [.fields] node, if it exists.
 * 
 * Use cases:
 * - Extracting the value of a [.fields] input node in HTTP endpoints to process form or query data.
 * - Fetching configuration or settings stored in a [.fields] node for further computation.
 * - Passing the value of [.fields] as an argument to another slot or operation.
 */
get-value:x:@.fields
